The paper introduces a new architecture for text-to-speech synthesis using generative adversarial networks (GANs). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SD (Sound), which specifically deals with audio and speech processing. The paper also involves natural language processing (NLP) as it generates speech from text, which falls under cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper uses quantitative metrics to evaluate the performance of the model, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
